properties.areaDesc: Southern Meade Co Plains; Rapid City; Pennington Co Plains
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 12 at 4:52AM MST until February 12 at 2:00PM MST by NWS Rapid City SD
properties.description:
* WHAT...North winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts up to 50 mph
expected.

* WHERE...The Southern Meade County Plains, the Rapid City area
and the Pennington County Plains.

* WHEN...Until 2 PM MST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Sudden wind gusts can cause drivers to lose control,
especially in lightweight or high profile vehicles. Strong
winds can cause blowing dust, reduced visibility, and flying
debris.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Light snow continues to overspread the area
this morning. Strong winds will cause areas of blowing snow and
reduced visibility through the afternoon.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 2 PM MST THIS AFTERNOON
